# Project Standards

## Language & Framework

- TypeScript strict mode — no `any` types
- React 18 with functional components only
- styled-components for styling (use theme tokens, not hardcoded values)
- Vitest + React Testing Library for tests

## Code Style

- Named exports for components
- One component per file
- Props interface defined above the component
- Destructure props in function signature
- Use `const` arrow functions for components
- Prefer composition over inheritance

## Naming

- Components: PascalCase
- Files: PascalCase for components, camelCase for utilities
- Props interfaces: `ComponentNameProps`
- Styled components: descriptive names (e.g., `HeaderContainer`, not `Div1`)

## Testing

- Test behavior, not implementation
- Use `screen.getByRole` and `screen.getByText` over `getByTestId`
- Each test should be independent

## AI Usage

- Review all AI-generated code before accepting
- Prefer small, targeted prompts over large generation requests
- Write simple logic by hand (loops, conditionals, basic state)
- Use AI for boilerplate, complex APIs, and scaffolding
